<paragraph blockId="10.[136,1452,1490,2093]" pageId="10" pageNumber="238">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,393,1814,1840]" pageId="10" pageNumber="238">Taxonomic notes</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nordstedt" authorityYear="1870" box="[429,667,1814,1840]" class="Conjugatophyceae" family="Desmidiaceae" genus="Xanthidium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zygnematales" pageId="10" pageNumber="238" phylum="Charophyta" rank="species" species="trilobum">
<emphasis box="[429,667,1814,1840]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="238">Xanthidium trilobum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Nordstedt, C. F. O." box="[889,1146,1814,1840]" pageId="10" pageNumber="238" pagination="195 - 234" refId="ref8518" refString="Nordstedt, C. F. O. (1870) Symbolae ad floram Brasiliae centralis cognoscendam. Videnskabelige meddelelser fra Dansk naturhistorisk forening i KObenhaven 21: 195 - 234." type="journal article" year="1870">Nordstedt (1870: 230)</bibRefCitation>
based on specimens from Lagoa Santa (
<collectingRegion box="[293,452,1850,1877]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="10" pageNumber="238">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
). This species is characterized by the presence of trilobate semicells angles with forked spines, and a central protrusion on the face of semicells ornamented by granules.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[136,1452,1490,2093]" lastBlockId="11.[136,1452,158,832]" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="239" pageId="10" pageNumber="238">
